1
00:00:16.549 --> 00:00:17.982
Come on.

2
00:00:39.194 --> 00:00:43.358
Kamajors. Local militia
protecting their homes, huh?

3
00:00:43.531 --> 00:00:45.396
- Do not look them in the eye.
- No.

4
00:00:59.881 --> 00:01:01.371
Excuse me. Excuse me?

5
00:01:02.317 --> 00:01:05.684
Hi, I'm Maddy Bowen
with <i>Vital Affairs</i> magazine.

6
00:01:05.854 --> 00:01:08.914
Wonder if I could take your picture.
I'm just gonna get my camera.

7
00:01:09.090 --> 00:01:12.025
I've heard about your struggle.
I'd love to know more about it.

8
00:01:12.193 --> 00:01:14.821
Would you mind if I took your picture?
Everyone together?

9
00:01:15.163 --> 00:01:16.926
Everyone could all come in together.

10
00:01:20.435 --> 00:01:22.460
Is that okay?
If everyone could come closer.

11
00:01:23.505 --> 00:01:26.599
If you come over here and come in
nice and close. That's good.

12
00:01:26.775 --> 00:01:30.233
Yeah. That's great.
And we'll get one with all of us.

13
00:01:30.512 --> 00:01:32.309
There you go. That's perfect.

14
00:01:34.115 --> 00:01:36.640
How about one together?
Us together, what do you think?

15
00:01:36.818 --> 00:01:38.786
I'll come in like this, yeah?

16
00:01:39.587 --> 00:01:40.576
Cheese.

17
00:01:42.757 --> 00:01:45.089
So do you think
they've read your work?

18
00:01:45.260 --> 00:01:47.387
Shut up.

19
00:02:00.275 --> 00:02:02.607
Hey, get them, get them, get them.

20
00:02:04.245 --> 00:02:07.942
- I got a score. I got a score.
- You missed.

21
00:02:08.650 --> 00:02:10.811
Where have you come from?

22
00:02:11.386 --> 00:02:14.116
- Where did you come from?
- Where have you come from?

23
00:02:15.223 --> 00:02:18.056
That's right. Yeah.
From New York. From America.

24
00:02:18.226 --> 00:02:20.126
I don't have anything for you.

25
00:02:40.448 --> 00:02:42.245
My name is Benjamin Margai.

26
00:02:42.951 --> 00:02:45.010
Danny Archer. This is Maddy Bowen.

27
00:02:45.186 --> 00:02:48.246
- Hello. How are you?
- Very well, thank you.

28
00:03:03.071 --> 00:03:05.369
I'm the cameraman?

29
00:03:07.976 --> 00:03:10.911
The Belgians were the first
to chop off limbs in Africa.

30
00:03:11.079 --> 00:03:15.448
King Leopold took one hand
for every hundredth slave in the Congo...

31
00:03:15.617 --> 00:03:17.710
...to keep them in line.

32
00:03:18.353 --> 00:03:21.288
Many of these children
were taken by the RUF.

33
00:03:21.456 --> 00:03:23.447
We have taken them back.

34
00:03:23.625 --> 00:03:26.719
Some of them have been
made to do horrible things.

35
00:03:26.895 --> 00:03:29.921
We are trying
to bring them back to life.

36
00:03:30.098 --> 00:03:31.725
Let me show you.

37
00:03:33.768 --> 00:03:36.066
Imagine doing all this, huh?

38
00:03:37.372 --> 00:03:39.272
What's your excuse?

39
00:03:40.074 --> 00:03:45.410
Well, it's gotten hard to go back
to sipping lattes and talking interest rates.

40
00:03:45.647 --> 00:03:48.275
So you're an action junkie, huh?

41
00:03:49.217 --> 00:03:51.515
Three out of five ex-boyfriends
recently polled...

42
00:03:51.686 --> 00:03:56.123
...say that I prefer to be
in a constant state of crisis.

43
00:03:56.658 --> 00:03:58.922
Maybe I just give a shit.

44
00:04:02.597 --> 00:04:03.586
You were good today.

45
00:04:06.034 --> 00:04:07.365
You know that?

46
00:04:08.503 --> 00:04:09.993
You too.

47
00:04:12.941 --> 00:04:15.876
"...that sometimes they forgot
to close the door.

48
00:04:16.044 --> 00:04:19.104
She also wrote
about her sister Josie...

49
00:04:19.714 --> 00:04:24.708
...who was very ill
and who had to be taken to hospital."

50
00:04:26.754 --> 00:04:27.948
Cheers.

51
00:04:30.758 --> 00:04:33.352
So how many attacks
have there been in the area?

52
00:04:33.528 --> 00:04:36.429
I have known most of the rebels
since they were children.

53
00:04:36.598 --> 00:04:41.126
The local commander is still afraid
I will come after him with my ruler.

54
00:04:42.570 --> 00:04:46.028
So you think because your intentions
are good, they'll spare you, huh?

55
00:04:46.207 --> 00:04:49.040
My heart always told me
that people are inherently good.

56
00:04:49.210 --> 00:04:51.405
My experience suggests otherwise.

57
00:04:51.579 --> 00:04:53.376
But what about you, Mr. Archer?

58
00:04:53.815 --> 00:04:56.249
In your long career as a journalist...

59
00:04:56.417 --> 00:04:59.250
...would you say that people
are mostly good?

60
00:05:01.322 --> 00:05:02.755
No.

61
00:05:03.024 --> 00:05:04.548
I'd say they're just people.

62
00:05:04.726 --> 00:05:08.662
Exactly. It is what they do
that makes them good or bad.

63
00:05:08.830 --> 00:05:12.061
A moment of love,
even in a bad man...

64
00:05:12.333 --> 00:05:14.801
...can give meaning to a life.

65
00:05:14.969 --> 00:05:18.598
None of us knows which path
will lead us to God.

66
00:05:21.342 --> 00:05:22.832
Hey!

67
00:06:10.825 --> 00:06:12.690
It's palm wine.

68
00:06:21.969 --> 00:06:24.904
- Jesus Christ.
- Yeah, yeah. It takes getting used to, huh?

69
00:06:25.073 --> 00:06:26.563
God.

70
00:06:26.741 --> 00:06:29.471
- Drank that as a boy.
- In Rhodesia?

71
00:06:31.646 --> 00:06:32.874
I take notes.

72
00:06:35.583 --> 00:06:37.312
The Shona...

73
00:06:38.619 --> 00:06:40.917
The Shona have a word for me.

74
00:06:42.757 --> 00:06:46.386
- It means "white boy in Africa."
- When did you leave?

75
00:06:47.028 --> 00:06:48.723
I didn't leave.

76
00:06:48.896 --> 00:06:53.230
I got sent away to South Africa
in 1978 when the <i>munts</i> overran us.

77
00:06:53.568 --> 00:06:55.035
Then you joined the army?

78
00:06:57.905 --> 00:07:00.066
Yeah. Yeah, I did my time in Angola.

79
00:07:00.241 --> 00:07:02.937
- The 32 Battalion.
- That's right.

80
00:07:05.313 --> 00:07:08.578
You know, contrary to what
you might think about us...

81
00:07:08.750 --> 00:07:12.242
...we fought with the blacks, huh?
Yeah. Side by side.

82
00:07:12.420 --> 00:07:16.151
There was no apartheid in a foxhole.
The colonel always used to tell us that.

83
00:07:16.324 --> 00:07:19.725
- This is Colonel Coetzee?
- Yeah.

84
00:07:21.963 --> 00:07:25.364
Then, of course, it's 1994.
No more army.

85
00:07:25.533 --> 00:07:27.364
No more apartheid.

86
00:07:27.535 --> 00:07:30.902
Truth and reconciliation
and all of that rubbish, you know.

87
00:07:31.072 --> 00:07:32.562
Kumbaya.

88
00:07:33.341 --> 00:07:36.105
We fought and died together,
you know?

89
00:07:36.277 --> 00:07:39.542
Black and white. Most people back home
didn't even know we were at war.

90
00:07:39.714 --> 00:07:41.579
We thought we were
fighting Communism...

91
00:07:41.749 --> 00:07:45.617
...but in the end, it was all about
who gets what, you know?

92
00:07:45.787 --> 00:07:48.847
Lvory, oil, gold:

93
00:07:49.791 --> 00:07:51.554
Diamonds.

94
00:07:54.796 --> 00:07:57.765
So one day I decided,
"Fuck it," you know?

95
00:07:58.399 --> 00:07:59.957
"I'm gonna get mine."

96
00:08:00.134 --> 00:08:01.726
You gonna steal his diamond?

97
00:08:09.243 --> 00:08:12.940
That diamond is my ticket
out of this godforsaken continent.

98
00:08:13.147 --> 00:08:14.978
That doesn't answer the question.

99
00:08:25.626 --> 00:08:29.722
My dad came home
from the war in '69.

100
00:08:31.999 --> 00:08:33.864
And it took him...

101
00:08:35.002 --> 00:08:37.095
...about 20 years to get right.

102
00:08:38.973 --> 00:08:40.270
What?

103
00:08:43.144 --> 00:08:47.444
You Americans love to talk
about your feelings, huh?

104
00:08:47.615 --> 00:08:49.879
So, what does that mean?
What does that mean?

105
00:08:50.051 --> 00:08:52.178
- Got a thing for messed-up vets now?
- Shut up.

106
00:08:54.188 --> 00:08:55.655
You lost both your parents.

107
00:08:56.557 --> 00:08:59.390
That's a polite way
of putting it, yeah.

108
00:09:02.029 --> 00:09:04.361
Mom was raped and shot...

109
00:09:07.201 --> 00:09:10.295
...and Dad was decapitated
and hung from a hook in the barn.

110
00:09:11.839 --> 00:09:13.568
I was 9.

111
00:09:17.178 --> 00:09:18.770
Boohoo, right?

112
00:09:22.517 --> 00:09:24.644
Sometimes I wonder...

113
00:09:27.755 --> 00:09:30.815
...will God ever forgive us
for what we've done to each other?

114
00:09:34.462 --> 00:09:37.329
Then I look around and I realize...

115
00:09:38.232 --> 00:09:41.690
...God left this place a long time ago.

116
00:09:48.409 --> 00:09:50.434
It's...

117
00:09:52.713 --> 00:09:54.647
What's the point, huh?

118
00:10:38.092 --> 00:10:40.117
Oh, shit. Keep moving, huh?

119
00:10:40.294 --> 00:10:42.057
- What?
- Drive at them. They'll panic.

120
00:10:42.229 --> 00:10:44.493
Do you know where the word
"infantry" comes from?

121
00:10:44.665 --> 00:10:47.964
It means "child soldier."
They are just children.

122
00:10:48.135 --> 00:10:51.798
- Stop! Stop! RUF on the road!
- Hi. Hello. Hello.

123
00:10:53.040 --> 00:10:54.098
Hello, little brothers.

124
00:10:54.275 --> 00:10:56.800
- RUF on the road!
- Yeah, yeah. What is your names?

125
00:10:57.311 --> 00:10:59.609
I'm Dead Body.
Who is this motherfucker?

126
00:10:59.780 --> 00:11:01.441
We are teachers on our way to Kono.

127
00:11:01.616 --> 00:11:03.846
Only RUF on the road.

128
00:11:04.018 --> 00:11:05.952
- RUF only!
- Yes, yes, I understand that.

129
00:11:06.153 --> 00:11:07.484
- Only RUF!
- But son, this is...

130
00:11:09.757 --> 00:11:11.349
Don't move! Don't move! Fuck.

131
00:11:13.594 --> 00:11:16.927
Jesus Christ! Maddy, press your hand
against the exit wound there, huh?

132
00:11:17.098 --> 00:11:19.396
- Got it.
- Keep it there, huh?

133
00:11:19.567 --> 00:11:21.330
Whatever you do,
don't talk, all right?

134
00:11:21.502 --> 00:11:23.333
Is there any wine left in that jug?

135
00:11:23.504 --> 00:11:25.369
- Here.
- Pour it all over everything, huh?

136
00:11:26.907 --> 00:11:29.842
The colonel's gonna have a medic
at the airstrip in Kono.

137
00:11:30.011 --> 00:11:33.003
- How far is it?
- You said not to talk.

138
00:11:33.280 --> 00:11:34.474
A comedian, huh?

139
00:11:48.663 --> 00:11:51.063
- How's his pulse?
- I can feel it sometimes.

140
00:12:01.509 --> 00:12:04.478
- Hold it right there.
- Stop.

141
00:12:04.645 --> 00:12:05.873
Papers, please.

142
00:12:10.051 --> 00:12:11.279
Excuse me.

143
00:12:11.452 --> 00:12:14.387
I was just trying
to keep pressure on the wound.

144
00:12:14.555 --> 00:12:17.080
- He's lost a lot of blood.
- You'll be all right, huh?

145
00:12:17.758 --> 00:12:19.055
Will you?

146
00:12:19.760 --> 00:12:22.752
I'll check on him in the tent
in a little bit. Thank you.

147
00:12:22.997 --> 00:12:24.328
Hey.

148
00:12:24.865 --> 00:12:26.856
Look who's alive, eh?

149
00:12:27.034 --> 00:12:28.365
I told the H you'd be back.

150
00:12:30.337 --> 00:12:33.272
I'm afraid we're evacuating
all non-military personnel, miss.

151
00:12:33.441 --> 00:12:35.272
Transport touches down at 1600.

152
00:12:35.443 --> 00:12:37.206
She's with me, all right?

153
00:12:37.411 --> 00:12:41.074
No exceptions, pal. This is gonna be ugly.
Colonel doesn't want an audience.

154
00:12:41.248 --> 00:12:44.046
Is I.R.'s presence here
known to other African nations?

155
00:12:45.553 --> 00:12:47.578
- She's with you?
- Yeah.

156
00:12:48.723 --> 00:12:50.588
Come on. The colonel's this way.

157
00:12:50.758 --> 00:12:52.589
Give me a minute, huh?

158
00:12:55.763 --> 00:12:58.288
We block their escape
by blowing the bridge.

159
00:12:59.934 --> 00:13:01.629
That's correct.

160
00:13:02.369 --> 00:13:04.667
You made it out. Well done.

161
00:13:04.872 --> 00:13:06.806
Negative, Kilo Foxtrot, stand by.

162
00:13:07.475 --> 00:13:11.138
- Colonel, sir.
- So must be real, then.

163
00:13:12.313 --> 00:13:13.507
The pink.

164
00:13:14.014 --> 00:13:16.608
Well, you're part
of this operation now.

165
00:13:16.784 --> 00:13:20.276
First we snuff everything that moves
out there, then we find your diamond.

166
00:13:20.454 --> 00:13:22.081
Colonel?

167
00:13:22.623 --> 00:13:25.057
Go get kitted. Yes?

168
00:13:31.365 --> 00:13:33.356
Move, move, move!

169
00:13:33.567 --> 00:13:36.832
- Go get your kit.
- Will do, chum. Will do.

170
00:13:40.374 --> 00:13:43.537
It's go time, all right?
Meet me behind the tents.

171
00:13:46.647 --> 00:13:48.342
How's Benjamin?

172
00:13:48.516 --> 00:13:49.983
They say he'll live.

173
00:13:51.318 --> 00:13:52.580
Good. Good.

174
00:13:59.994 --> 00:14:01.791
Listen, Maddy...

175
00:14:03.197 --> 00:14:04.960
...I need you to do me one last favor.

176
00:14:06.000 --> 00:14:07.365
Yeah?

177
00:14:09.336 --> 00:14:10.997
Tell that guard
you wanna put him...

178
00:14:11.172 --> 00:14:13.834
...on the cover of <i>Soldier of Fortune</i>
magazine for me.

179
00:14:19.880 --> 00:14:21.108
You're going in.

180
00:14:25.519 --> 00:14:27.783
You and Solomon.

181
00:14:29.957 --> 00:14:30.946
You're going in now.

182
00:14:31.792 --> 00:14:33.987
Your plane leaves
in a few minutes, huh?

183
00:14:36.597 --> 00:14:38.565
You're an idiot.

184
00:14:42.870 --> 00:14:45.737
- What if I wanted to go in with you?
- I'd say no.

185
00:14:45.906 --> 00:14:47.897
- What if I insist?
- I'd insist back.

186
00:14:54.014 --> 00:14:55.208
It's my story.

187
00:14:55.382 --> 00:14:58.783
Your story is Van De Kaap, all right?
That stone is mine.

188
00:14:58.953 --> 00:15:02.389
I'm not leaving here without it,
you understand?

189
00:15:03.858 --> 00:15:06.725
Please, just give me two minutes.

190
00:15:23.477 --> 00:15:24.876
Yeah.

191
00:15:36.190 --> 00:15:37.885
- Hello.
- Hi.

192
00:15:38.058 --> 00:15:41.289
My name is Maddy Bowen.
I'm with <i>Vital Affairs</i> magazine.

193
00:15:41.462 --> 00:15:43.930
I was wondering
if I could ask you a few questions.

194
00:15:44.098 --> 00:15:45.622
Well, that depends what they are.

195
00:15:45.799 --> 00:15:49.758
Oh, I see you're familiar
with our devious ways, aren't you?

196
00:15:50.504 --> 00:15:52.404
Okay, so I'll start
with something simple.

197
00:16:05.019 --> 00:16:07.681
And before that you were with
the South African Defense...?

198
00:16:07.855 --> 00:16:09.516
- Defense Force, correct.
- Of course.

199
00:16:09.690 --> 00:16:13.126
And was that with Colonel Coetzee?
Were you in Angola?

200
00:16:13.294 --> 00:16:14.818
Angola, yeah.

201
00:16:16.430 --> 00:16:19.399
That is all I really need to know.
Thank you so much.

202
00:16:19.600 --> 00:16:21.067
- Thank you.
- Okay.

203
00:16:31.078 --> 00:16:32.477
Thank you, huh?

204
00:16:32.646 --> 00:16:35.080
Just keeping my end of the deal.

205
00:16:35.683 --> 00:16:36.980
Good luck to you, Solomon.

206
00:16:37.284 --> 00:16:38.774
Okay.

207
00:16:39.954 --> 00:16:43.788
- I hope you find what you're looking for.
- Thank you for all you have done.

208
00:16:51.231 --> 00:16:53.825
- Listen, l...
- No, you listen.

209
00:16:58.439 --> 00:17:00.339
In another life maybe, all right?

210
00:17:01.775 --> 00:17:03.606
Yeah. Sure.

211
00:17:03.777 --> 00:17:05.142
Yeah.

212
00:17:09.483 --> 00:17:11.610
You find yourself a good man,
all right, Maddy?

213
00:17:17.558 --> 00:17:20.584
You know, I've got three sisters.

214
00:17:20.761 --> 00:17:23.389
They're all married to good men.

215
00:17:25.265 --> 00:17:26.323
I prefer my life.

216
00:17:28.969 --> 00:17:33.429
Here is my office phone...

217
00:17:33.607 --> 00:17:35.973
...home phone, cell phone.

218
00:17:38.078 --> 00:17:41.241
I'm used to being pursued,
but what the heck.

219
00:17:52.426 --> 00:17:54.553
You better get on that plane, huh?

220
00:17:56.296 --> 00:17:58.196
You should get on that plane.

221
00:18:06.373 --> 00:18:08.170
So should you.

222
00:18:14.648 --> 00:18:15.774
You gonna call me?

223
00:18:19.586 --> 00:18:21.076
Soon as I'm near a phone, yeah.

224
00:18:22.022 --> 00:18:24.388
Yeah, right.

225
00:18:46.213 --> 00:18:49.478
- Where is he?
- I don't know.

226
00:18:54.054 --> 00:18:55.646
Oh, shit.

227
00:18:55.923 --> 00:18:58.653
Nabil? Yeah, I'll call you
when we get closer, all right?

228
00:18:58.826 --> 00:19:01.420
You keep me posted. Right.

229
00:19:01.595 --> 00:19:05.395
All right. I set the pace, huh?
Two-hour marches, five-minute breaks.

230
00:19:05.566 --> 00:19:09.400
If I hold my hand up like this, you stop.
If I point to the dirt, you lie flat.

231
00:19:09.570 --> 00:19:13.131
If I say go, you move like your life
depended on it. Understood?

232
00:19:13.307 --> 00:19:15.969
- Yes, boss.
- Come on.

233
00:19:26.253 --> 00:19:27.914
Tell me about the stone.

234
00:19:28.088 --> 00:19:30.716
Is it clear or is it milky?

235
00:19:30.891 --> 00:19:32.415
Clear.

236
00:19:32.593 --> 00:19:34.993
And the color, is it strong?

237
00:19:35.162 --> 00:19:36.390
Does it hold the light?

238
00:19:36.563 --> 00:19:38.622
It is as you say.

239
00:19:39.066 --> 00:19:42.229
- About the size of a bird's egg?
- Yes.

240
00:19:42.402 --> 00:19:46.566
One hundred carats.
Come on, let's pick up the pace.

241
00:20:28.148 --> 00:20:29.513
Dia!

242
00:20:31.418 --> 00:20:33.386
Stop the truck!

243
00:20:34.154 --> 00:20:35.849
I thought it was Dia.

244
00:21:29.776 --> 00:21:31.334
Wake up.

245
00:21:33.180 --> 00:21:36.274
Don't worry, they're gone, huh?

246
00:21:37.618 --> 00:21:40.746
You know, I once had this buddy...

247
00:21:40.921 --> 00:21:42.786
...named Mabhoko.

248
00:21:43.557 --> 00:21:46.788
We used to hunt bush meat
together as kids, huh?

249
00:21:47.594 --> 00:21:48.959
Baboons.

250
00:21:49.129 --> 00:21:51.996
Baboons, they were
