You are a good boy
who loves soccer and school.

504
00:46:27.139 --> 00:46:30.267
Your mother loves you so much.

505
00:46:32.711 --> 00:46:35.509
She waits by the fire making plantains...

506
00:46:35.681 --> 00:46:38.343
...and red palm oil stew
with your sister N'Yanda...

507
00:46:40.619 --> 00:46:42.883
...and the new baby.

508
00:46:51.797 --> 00:46:54.061
The cows wait for you.

509
00:46:54.233 --> 00:47:00.035
And Babu, the wild dog
who minds no one but you.

510
00:47:02.608 --> 00:47:05.941
I know they made you do bad things...

511
00:47:06.111 --> 00:47:08.579
...but you are not a bad boy.

512
00:47:11.784 --> 00:47:14.184
I am your father...

513
00:47:15.888 --> 00:47:18.186
...who loves you.

514
00:47:19.458 --> 00:47:23.224
And you will come home with me
and be my son again.

515
00:47:48.654 --> 00:47:51.020
Solomon, we've got to move, huh?

516
00:47:51.190 --> 00:47:52.748
We've got to...

517
00:47:55.928 --> 00:47:58.624
Go, go! Move!

518
00:48:01.400 --> 00:48:02.958
Move. Move.

519
00:48:03.135 --> 00:48:04.432
Move, move, move!

520
00:48:04.603 --> 00:48:07.629
Move! Move! Move!

521
00:48:09.241 --> 00:48:10.469
How far?

522
00:48:10.642 --> 00:48:12.701
There's an airstrip
at the top of that gorge.

523
00:48:12.878 --> 00:48:14.971
A plane will meet us, huh?

524
00:48:15.380 --> 00:48:17.746
Hey, stop. Stop.

525
00:48:20.018 --> 00:48:24.011
Give it to me.
Come on, give it to me, huh?

526
00:48:31.530 --> 00:48:34.590
Keep moving. They'll be tracking us.

527
00:48:40.906 --> 00:48:42.965
Nabil, where are you?

528
00:48:44.042 --> 00:48:46.670
I'm nearly there.
Tell me what's happening.

529
00:48:46.845 --> 00:48:50.303
We're about 10 K's out, huh?
We've got it, my friend.

530
00:48:50.482 --> 00:48:52.382
- <i>Who is we?</i>
- The fisherman and his son.

531
00:48:52.551 --> 00:48:54.143
<i>Lose them.</i>

532
00:49:08.300 --> 00:49:10.393
It's at the top of that ridge there, huh?

533
00:49:10.569 --> 00:49:11.866
You must stop and rest.

534
00:49:12.037 --> 00:49:14.870
What? And give up the damn stone?

535
00:49:15.040 --> 00:49:17.099
Keep moving. Come on.

536
00:49:51.743 --> 00:49:54.075
Come. Come, come.

537
00:50:41.193 --> 00:50:43.491
I can't. Stop.

538
00:50:43.662 --> 00:50:45.721
- Okay.
- Stop.

539
00:51:14.192 --> 00:51:15.284
Come on.

540
00:51:15.894 --> 00:51:18.488
No! God, no. Stop.

541
00:51:19.598 --> 00:51:22.931
Christ. No more. No more.

542
00:52:06.878 --> 00:52:08.573
Take it, huh?

543
00:52:10.982 --> 00:52:14.179
- Mr. Archer...
- Take it, take it.

544
00:52:21.259 --> 00:52:23.022
I thought you would steal it from me.

545
00:52:24.863 --> 00:52:28.492
Yeah, yeah, it occurred to me, huh?

546
00:52:39.444 --> 00:52:41.071
Listen...

547
00:52:44.049 --> 00:52:46.449
...this is Maddy's card, huh?

548
00:52:46.618 --> 00:52:48.779
You call her when
you get to Conakry, all right?

549
00:52:53.024 --> 00:52:54.992
And don't trust that pilot for a second.

550
00:52:55.160 --> 00:52:58.220
You point this at his head
if he fucks around, all right?

551
00:52:58.396 --> 00:52:59.863
I can carry you.

552
00:53:12.777 --> 00:53:14.244
You take your boy home, huh?

553
00:53:19.417 --> 00:53:22.079
You take him home, huh?

554
00:53:26.691 --> 00:53:28.454
- Go! Go!
- Go. Come on.

555
00:53:29.294 --> 00:53:30.386
Go on!

556
00:53:36.134 --> 00:53:37.999
Come on. Come on.

557
00:53:44.809 --> 00:53:47.175
Archer, you're a dead man!

558
00:53:47.345 --> 00:53:49.176
Yeah, yeah.

559
00:54:19.878 --> 00:54:21.243
Dia.

560
00:54:42.467 --> 00:54:43.627
Hello. Maddy Bowen.

561
00:54:43.868 --> 00:54:45.699
Yeah.

562
00:54:46.037 --> 00:54:47.698
Thought I'd never call, huh?

563
00:54:48.607 --> 00:54:52.668
And I'm so glad you did.
Excuse me.

564
00:54:54.646 --> 00:54:55.806
When am I gonna see you?

565
00:54:56.948 --> 00:55:02.682
Maddy, I want you to do me
one more favor, huh?

566
00:55:03.388 --> 00:55:07.916
I want you to go meet Solomon
in Conakry.

567
00:55:08.126 --> 00:55:10.822
In Guinea?
Why do you want me to go to Guinea?

568
00:55:13.832 --> 00:55:15.891
We found his son...

569
00:55:16.868 --> 00:55:20.269
...but he's gonna need some help,
you understand?

570
00:55:21.039 --> 00:55:22.131
<i>Maddy?</i>

571
00:55:24.943 --> 00:55:26.808
You're hurt.

572
00:55:27.445 --> 00:55:28.503
Are you hurt?

573
00:55:28.680 --> 00:55:31.843
Yeah, well, I've got
a little problem here.

574
00:55:36.421 --> 00:55:40.118
Okay. You...
You tell me where you are.

575
00:55:43.395 --> 00:55:44.419
<i>Archer?</i>

576
00:55:56.574 --> 00:56:01.307
I'm looking at an incredible view
right now.

577
00:56:02.714 --> 00:56:04.341
I wish you were here, Maddy.

578
00:56:04.516 --> 00:56:08.179
Okay, then I'm coming to be with you.
You just tell me where you are.

579
00:56:11.389 --> 00:56:12.720
I don't think so.

580
00:56:12.891 --> 00:56:16.224
Are you still in Kono? Because I can
get someone there to help you.

581
00:56:16.394 --> 00:56:20.660
Maddy, you find someplace safe
for the boy, all right?

582
00:56:20.832 --> 00:56:23.232
<i>And keep him out of sight.</i>

583
00:56:23.835 --> 00:56:26.565
<i>And get Solomon to London.</i>

584
00:56:29.708 --> 00:56:32.472
He's bringing something with him.

585
00:56:33.144 --> 00:56:35.078
But he's gonna need your help.

586
00:56:36.314 --> 00:56:38.145
Why aren't you bringing it yourself?

587
00:56:39.651 --> 00:56:44.714
I'm saying it's a real story now.

588
00:56:45.623 --> 00:56:47.352
And you can write the hell out of it.

589
00:56:54.566 --> 00:56:57.091
I'm really happy I met you.

590
00:56:58.670 --> 00:56:59.659
You know that?

591
00:57:03.007 --> 00:57:05.134
Yeah, I'm...

592
00:57:06.344 --> 00:57:09.404
I'm really happy I met you too.

593
00:57:10.014 --> 00:57:14.007
<i>And I wish I could be there with you.</i>

594
00:57:14.886 --> 00:57:16.854
That's all right.

595
00:57:19.391 --> 00:57:21.791
I'm exactly where I'm supposed to be.

596
00:58:15.413 --> 00:58:17.745
When we get to the stairs,
you just keep walking...

597
00:58:17.916 --> 00:58:19.941
...and I'll wait for you here.

598
00:58:20.518 --> 00:58:22.042
You're not coming.

599
00:58:22.220 --> 00:58:25.485
I'm not here. Good luck.

600
00:58:47.145 --> 00:58:49.807
You must understand, Mr. Vandy...

601
00:58:49.981 --> 00:58:56.045
...that your diamond could have ended up
nowhere else but with us.

602
00:58:59.357 --> 00:59:02.326
- It is not enough.
- I assure you, 2 million pounds...

603
00:59:02.494 --> 00:59:06.362
...is more than anyone else will offer you
for that stone under the circumstances.

604
00:59:06.531 --> 00:59:09.227
I want what was promised to me
by Mr. Archer.

605
00:59:12.704 --> 00:59:15.229
- What was promised to you?
- My family.

606
00:59:15.573 --> 00:59:17.564
When they are here,
you will get the stone.

607
00:59:18.243 --> 00:59:19.870
I will have the money too.

608
00:59:21.179 --> 00:59:22.703
Well, may I see what I'm buying?

609
00:59:22.881 --> 00:59:25.645
You will get the stone
once my family is here.

610
00:59:26.417 --> 00:59:28.214
How do I even know you've got it?

611
01:01:36.114 --> 01:01:38.878
Can you comment on the diamonds
mined in Sierra Leone?

612
01:01:39.050 --> 01:01:42.952
I'm not going to comment
on some sensationalist magazine article.

613
01:01:43.121 --> 01:01:45.715
- What about Liberia?
- No comment. No comment.

614
01:01:45.890 --> 01:01:48.290
- Mr. Van De Kaap...
- That's all I have to say.

615
01:01:48.459 --> 01:01:49.858
The natural resources
of a country...

616
01:01:51.863 --> 01:01:54.832
...are the property of its people.
They are not ours to steal...

617
01:01:56.167 --> 01:02:01.628
<i>... or exploit in the name of our comfort,</i>
<i>our corporations, or our consumerism.</i>

618
01:02:11.549 --> 01:02:13.608
They're ready for you, sir.

619
01:02:15.119 --> 01:02:17.519
The Third World is not a world apart.

620
01:02:17.689 --> 01:02:22.353
And the witness you will hear today
speaks on its behalf.

621
01:02:22.527 --> 01:02:26.395
Let us hear the voice of that world.
Let us learn from that voice.

622
01:02:26.564 --> 01:02:30.091
And let us ignore it no more.

623
01:02:30.268 --> 01:02:33.601
Ladies and gentlemen,
Mr. Solomon Vandy.

624
01:12:21.859 --> 01:12:23.850
[ENGLISH]

